name: Slow Cooker Honey Barbeque Ranch Wings
author: Michael Rodgerson
summary: Moist and tasty chicken wings that can go with anything. I could see these going well with rice.
ingredients: 1 ½ cups barbeque sauce (such as Sweet Baby Ray's®)
3 (1 ounce) packages ranch dressing mix (such as Hidden Valley Ranch®)
directions: Mix barbeque sauce, honey, and ranch dressing together in a large bowl
Dip wings in the sauce until coated
Transfer wings to a 6-quart slow cooker; pour any remaining sauce on top
Cook on High until no longer pink at the bone and the juices run clear, about 4 hours
An instant-read thermometer inserted near the bone should read 165 degrees F (74 degrees C)
